Package nl.tue.multibrowsertest

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CapabilitiesProvider
    Provides a list of DesiredCapabilities to an instance of MultiBrowserTester.
    CrossBrowserTest<ResultObject>
    This interface can be implemented by Selenium browser tests who need to be tested with various browsers.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    MultiBrowserTester<ResultObject>
    Test-class used to run a Selenium browser-test concurrently on multiple remote browsers.
    MultiBrowserTester.ResultTriple<ResultObject>
    Data class containing the ResultObject of a specific browser with a specific Dimension.
    TestRunner<ResultObject>
    A test-runner capable of running a standard Selenium browser test given a browser to test against, a Dimension the browser should have, a CrossBrowserTest to run and an location of the host to run the test on.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    MultiBrowserTesterException
    Generic Exception class thrown if there is an error with the MultiBrowserTester.
